main event: Two fish-shaped, oblong objects were sighted in the sky, one half a mile behind the other. The objects suddenly faded from view.
interesting points: The objects were described as fish-shaped and oblong.
The objects were close to each other, with one object half a mile behind the other.
The objects suddenly faded from view after being observed for about 1 minute.
The observer stated that the same visual presentation had been noticed on at least three previous occasions by six or more different individuals, all Ground Observer Corps personnel.
It was concluded that the sightings represented flights of two aircraft in trail formation.
result: Possibly identified as aircraft in trail formation
